<HEADLINE> Senior Chinese Extends Sympathy to People in Typhoon-stricken Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Jiang Chunyun, who
is also a member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee
of the Communist Party of China, today extended his concern and
sympathy to people in the typhoon-stricken areas in east China.
</P>
<P>
Jiang was on an inspection tour out of Beijing. He called
authorities in the area several times yesterday for updates on the
damage that occurred during the strong typhoon which swept over
six provinces and a municipality in east China on Monday.
</P>
<P>
As head of China's national anti-flood and drought control
headquarters, Jiang urged local people to work hard and
self-reliantly and required departments concerned to repair the
damaged facilities and to help people get their lives back in
order after the disaster.
</P>
<P>
A strong typhoon, accompanied with thunderstorms and tidal
waves, hit east China's Zhejiang, Jiangsu, Fujian, Anhui, Shandong
provinces and Shanghai in the last two days.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the timely warning about the typhoon, nicknamed
Winnie, the damage was greatly reduced.
</P>
<P>
After the typhoon, rain fell in north China, easing the drought
in the region.  
</P>
</TEXT>
