<HEADLINE> Exported Computer System for Nuclear Power Station Passes Appraisal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 20 (Xinhua) -- A China-developed computer
system to be installed in a nuclear power plant in Pakistan today
passed appraisal.
</P>
<P>
Sources said it was the first time for China to export a
computer system for a nuclear power station.
</P>
<P>
The system will be installed in a Pakistan-based plant with the
generation capacity of 300,000 kw, to be built by a Chinese
company in the country.
</P>
<P>
The Helishi Automatic Engineering Co., developer of the system,
also won the bid to design a computer system for the second phase
expansion of Qinshan Nuclear Power Station, China's first nuclear
power plant, sources added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
