<HEADLINE> Indian Police Seize 7 kg Heroin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Indian police seized seven
kilograms of heroin in the Capital on Tuesday night, Press Trust
of India reported today.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, three members of an inter-state gang of drug
smugglers have been arrested, police said.
</P>
<P>
Acting on a tip off that a gang was regularly bringing
contraband to Delhi and that a huge consignment was to be
delivered in an area in the capital, a 15-member team of the
special cell kept vigil in the area for two weeks.
</P>
<P>
The corps on Tuesday night spotted a car in suspicious
circumstances in the area and nabbed the accused, police said.
</P>
<P>
Seven packets of heroin were recovered from the vehicle.
</P>
<P>
Police said that the gang was operating in Delhi, Madhya
Pradesh, Rajasthan, Karnataka and Maharashtra.  
</P>
</TEXT>
