<HEADLINE> Christie Likely to Coach Italian Lang Jumper </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 20 (Xinhua) -- World and Olympic sprint champion
Linford Christie of Britain is likely to coach Italy's long
jumping star Fiona May, according to news from Milan on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
May, who was born in Slough but took Italian nationality after
moving here in 1993, has already sparked controversy by saying she
wants to quit the official Italian training center at Formia.
</P>
<P>
Christie is among her options as she looks for a new coach.
</P>
<P>
"I've known Linford since I was 17," said the 27-year-old. "And
when it comes down to it, he's already coaching Baulch, Campbell
and Fredericks part-time -- so he could give me a few tips."
</P>
