<HEADLINE> Germany Sweep Synchronised Diving Titles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Germany swept the inaugural
synchronised diving titles by finishing the top two in the men's
synchronised highboard at the European swimming championships in
Seville, Spain, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Jan Hempel, Monday's individual 10-meter platform gold
medalist, faced no impressive challenge to win the gold with
Michael Kuehne by 300.84 points, an unbeatable mark for Igor
Lukashin and Alexander Varlamov of Russia who were second with
272.40 points.
</P>
<P>
Claudia Bockner and Conny Schmalfuss narrowly beat Irina Lashko
and Yulia Pakhalina of Russia (267.96-264.24) in five dives to
clinch the title of the women's synchronised three-meter
springboard event.
</P>
<P>
The titles of men's three-meter and women's 10-meter in the new
synchronised series also went to the Germans.
</P>
<P>
Germany got six golds in the diving program, while Russia took
the other four. 
</P>
</TEXT>
