<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Profile: Ali Shamkhani, Iran's Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Ali Shamkhani, Iran's naval
commander, today became Minister of Defense and Armed Forces
Logistics in the new administration headed by liberal President
Mohammad Khatami.
</P>
<P>
Shamkhani secured 251 out of 266 votes from the 270-member
Parliament here this afternoon. He is one of the youngest in the
new cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Since he had served in the Islamic Revolution Guards Corps
(IRGC) for a long time, Shamkhani is believed to be a trusted
follower of Iran's Supreme Leader Ali Khamenei.
</P>
<P>
Shamkhani was born in the city of Ahvaz, Khuzestan province in
western Iran in 1955. He currently serves as the Commander of the
Naval Forces of the Army, the Islamic Revolution's Guard Corps
(IRGC), as well as Commander of Khatam ul-Anbia Naval
Headquarters in the Persian Gulf.
</P>
<P>
He also held various military posts during the eight-year
Iran-Iraq war (1980-88), including the commander of the IRGC
forces in Ahvaz, Khuzestan, acting commander of IRGC, commander
of IRGC ground forces, deputy in charge of information and
operations of the Armed Forces Headquarters, IRGC Minister and
the official in charge of the implementation of the
U.N. Resolution 598 on ending the Iran-Iraq war.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the open debate in the Parliament, Shamkhani declared
that he would give priorities in the action of plan to
strengthening the country's defensive power without posing any
threat to other countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that his plan of action was based on four
principles: recommendations of the late spiritual leader
Khomeini, guidelines of today's Supreme Leader Khamenei, the
programs announced by President Mohammad Khatami and the second
Five-Year Economic Development Plan (1995-1999).
</P>
<P>
Shamkhani, 42, said that comprehensive research on current legal
status of the Defense Ministry and drawing up a restructuring
plan for the ministry and its subsidiary organizations would be
among the programs to be followed by him.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he said, promotion of sophisticated technology in
defense related industries, export of defensive products,
renovation and modernization of strategic defense industries
would also be followed up seriously. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
