<HEADLINE> Britain Evacuates Volcano-ravaged Montserrat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The evacuation of the
volcano-ravaged eastern Caribbean island of Montserrat started
today, a spokesman for the British Foreign Office said.
</P>
<P>
The evacuees were being taken to the nearby islands of Antigua
and Guadeloupe by local ferry under the supervision of the British
warship, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"It is an orderly evacuation and people are not leaving in huge
numbers," he added.
</P>
<P>
Montserrat's volcano began hurling out rocks and ash in July
1995. The situation has worsened recently with 19 deaths in June
and the destruction of the capital, Plymouth, two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
Montserrat was a tourist destination. Its population has fallen
from 11,000 before the volcanic activity to about 5,000.  
</P>
