<HEADLINE> Peace Process Breakdowns Hamper Refugee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Luanda, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The delays of the peace process
in Angola will hamper the program to settle the 500,000 war
refugees scheduled to finish by the end of the year, a senior
official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Alboino Malungo, Minister for Assistance and Social
Reinsertion made the remark when meeting with Joao Medina, the
visiting Cape Verde Minister for Health, Labor and Social
Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Malungo said that the continuous break-downs of the peace
process in Angola have given rise to distrust among the different
factions in the country, and thus make the planned settlement of
500,000 refugees difficult to materialize.
</P>
<P>
He said only about 250,000 refugees have been resettled so far
this year.
</P>
<P>
The 1.5 million refugees are in very bad conditions and the
refugee camps are often attacked and robbed by criminals, he
said, adding that many of the refugees have fled their camps.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Minister Medina said that Cape Verde and Angola
enjoy traditional ties of friendly cooperation and shall further
strengthen their relations.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two countries, facing different problems,
should help each other and learn from each other.
</P>
<P>
The Cape Verde minister had come here for a week-long visit.
</P>
</TEXT>
