<HEADLINE> S. Africa to Return Archives to Namibia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Archives, which were
brought to South Africa after Namibian independence in 1990, are
to be returned to Namibia, South African Arts and Culture
Minister Lionel Mtshali said today.
</P>
<P>
The South African cabinet had approved the return of the
archives relating to Namibia, Mtshali said.
</P>
<P>
The archives to be returned deal with the security management
system developed for the then South West Africa by the South
African government.
</P>
<P>
Some of the records are of a routine and administrative
nature, while others deal with South African cabinet memoranda,
proceedings of the Cabinet Committee on Constitutional Reform,
South African internal politics and security, and South African
international relations, Mtshali said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from professional considerations of archival integrity,
the motivations of confidentiality was no longer a valid
justification for keeping the records in South Africa, he said.
</P>
