<HEADLINE> ECLAC Bibliographic Data Installed on Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The Economic Commission
for Latin America and the Caribbean (ECLAC) had successfully
completed installation on the Internet of its bibliographic
database, the UN Department of Public Information reported today.
</P>
<P>
Covering documentation issued by the commission from 1948 to
the present, the database included ECLAC documents and
publications, as well as those of the Latin American and Caribbean
Institute for Economic and Social Planning and the Latin American
Demographic Center, published at the ECLAC headquarters in
Santiago, Chile, or at the ECLAC subregional headquarters and
national offices in the region.
</P>
<P>
