<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 20 (Xinhua) -- All three major stock markets in
Europe continued to recover from recent market jitters and closed
higher today, inspired by Wall Street's resilience and the
strength of the dollar.
</P>
<P>
On the London market, British shares extended Tuesday's rebound
and finished the day with solid gains, after Wall Street built on
its overnight rally.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that retail sales boosted the index of top shares
despite the interest rate implications of robust sales growth.
</P>
<P>
Banks, oils and drug stocks performed well, which took the FTSE
100 index up 44.2 points at 4,958.4 by the close of the session.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, the DAX-30 index was boosted by a robust
performance on Wall Street overnight and renewed dollar strength
and ended at 4,223.43, up 53.81 points.
</P>
<P>
On the Paris bourse, stocks remained strongly ahead and closed
near the day's highs on expectations of no change in German
interest rates. The CAC-40 index ended up 43.11 points at
2,979.27. 
