<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, August 21 (Xinhua) -- A ranking Chinese official
recently urged local officials in northeast China's Jilin Province
to abide by the rules of the market economy and give scope to local
advantages in a bid to accelerate the growth of the socialist
market economy.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua, who is also member of the Political
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China
(CPC), made the remark during his visit to major industrial
enterprises and research institutes in Jilin.
</P>
<P>
He urged local officials to have in mind overall economic
situation and the part that their local economy plays in the
country's economic development.
</P>
<P>
"A socialist market-oriented economy has to compete. The
competition, however, should be beneficial for the sustained,
sound and speedy development of China's national economy," he
said, adding that more should be done to exploit local advantages
during the process of local economic development.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Zou praised the efforts of the local government to
boost agricultural development in this leading grain production
province.
</P>
<P>
After an inspection of the First Auto Works Corporation and
Jilin Chemical Industrial Corporation, Zou charged these two
largest industrial enterprises to improve their marketing and
sales so as to put their most sought-after products onto the
market.  
