<HEADLINE> Chinese, Japanese People Should Live in Harmony: Vice-President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The people of China and Japan
should inherit and carry forward the cause of Sino-Japanese
friendship forged by the older generations, so that they can live
in permanent accord, Chinese Vice-President Rong Yiren said here
today.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with the visiting governor of Japan's Yamagata
Prefecture, Kazuo Takahashi, he said the friendship between the
Chinese and Japanese people has a long history, but a certain
period of history should not be forgotten in the relationship.
</P>
<P>
"In order to ensure a long-lasting friendship between Chinese
and Japanese people, it will be extremely important for the
younger generations to recognize the significance of a friendly
and cooperative Sino-Japanese relationship, and make due
contributions to its growth," Rong stressed.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Rong also congratulated the fruitful
exchanges and cooperation between Yamagata and China's northernmost
Heilongjiang Province since they forged the bond of sisterly ties.
</P>
<P>
Takahashi said this was the 14th goodwill visit of his
prefecture, and also the most significant one as this year marks
the 25th anniversary of the normalization of Sino-japanese ties.
</P>
<P>
Takahashi also said Yamagata will continue to organize visits
of this type to further the understanding and friendship between
the people of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Pointing to the successful cooperation in education, culture,
and sports with the Chinese sister province over the past five
years, Takahashi expressed his hope that exchanges and cooperation
with China will continue to grow.
</P>
<P>
The 141-member delegation, which arrived here Wednesday at the
invitation of the China International Trust and Investment
Corporation, are expected to travel to cities in Northwest and
Northeast China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
