<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Rise on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined mostly
on
the Singapore market, while the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index continued to rise, gaining 2.65 points to close
at 1946.57 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased marginally to 186.48 million
units, valued at 479.5 million Singapore dollars (about 317.55
million U.S. dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 250 to 79,
while 274 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Rekapac was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 21.19 million units. It was followed by Hotung which
had 18.43 million shares traded. The United Industrial Corporation
(UIC) was next with 9.09 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 2.9 dollars to finish at 35.1 Singapore
dollars. Car distributor Cycle &AMP; Carriage (C&AMP;C) gained 50 cents to
end at 11.7 Singapore dollars. City Developments warrant 98 closed
25 cents higher at 8.8 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign was
the biggest loser as it declined by 80 cents to end at 24.1
Singapore dollars. Sungei Way fell by 60 cents to close at 2.1
Singapore dollars, while Rekapac finished 47 cents lower at 1.19
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
