<HEADLINE> Viag Group Reports Surge in First-Half Pre-Tax Profits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Viag group said today its
first-half pre-tax profits surged 28 percent to 1.5 billion marks
(808 million U.S. dollars), and expected an "appreciable" rise in
profits this year despite start-up losses in its telecoms
business.
</P>
<P>
The Munich-based diversified industrial conglomerate reported a
12 percent growth in sales during the period, which reached 23.8
billion marks (12.8 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
Viag particularly attributed the improvement to the operating
profit increase at its power-generation unit Bayernwerk and its
chemicals division, SKW Trostberg.
</P>
<P>
Viag's main businesses are electricity generation, chemicals,
packaging and freight. 
