<HEADLINE> Russia Tightens Control over Foreign Arms Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
has signed a decree tightening control over foreign trade in the
military field, the presidential press service announced today.
</P>
<P>
Under the decree, three state corporations will be set up to
mediate all activities in the country's foreign military trade.
No other unit or corporation will be permitted to sell or buy
arms, military equipment or military technology directly to or
from foreign companies.
</P>
<P>
The three corporations are: the Corporation for the Importing
and Exporting of Arms, the Corporation for Exporting of Military
Industry and the Corporation for the Importing and Exporting of
Technology. 
</P>
</TEXT>
