<HEADLINE> China Executes Three Fake Value-Added Tax Receipt Sellers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The Supreme People's Court of
China today announced that three men convicted of selling fake
value-added tax receipts had been sentenced to death and were
executed today in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Chen Huan, Zhang Heping and Lu Dehua were also deprived of all
political rights as a result of their criminal activities.
</P>
<P>
Chen, a former tax supervisor in Shanghai municipality,
together with Zhang and Lu, sold 106 fake value-added tax receipts
amounting to 450 million yuan. The evaded state taxes hit 22.88
million yuan. The trio gained some 300,000 yuan of illegal
income.  
