<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzanian government
has allocated 5,000 acres of land to build an ultra modern
science complex near Langi Jabe, about 50 kilometers off Arusha
in northern Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
The ultra modern complex, the International Village for
Science and Technology (IVST), will comprise a library, a
university, a primary school, a computer center, a secondary
school, a technology center, an earth and atmospheric sciences
block, a report from Arusha said today.
