<HEADLINE> Coconut Export Earnings Increase in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Coconut export earnings of the
Philippines in June this year reached 104.56 million U.S. dollars,
97.8 percent higher than last year's 52.86 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Volume of exported copra also increased by 172.6 percent from
78,441 metric tons last year to 213,795 metric tons this year,
Philippine Coconut Authority Administrator Virgilio David
announced today in a press conference.
</P>
<P>
The performance shows that the coconut industry is now
recovering from the effects of the three super typhoons that hit
the country in late 1995, David said.
</P>
<P>
Export earnings from January to June, however, dropped by 3.1
percent from 422.7 million dollars in last year to 409.5 million
dollars in this year.
</P>
<P>
Volume of copra exported also declined by 3.14 percent from
last year's 745,939 metric tons to 722,545 metric tons, he said.
</P>
<P>
Coconut oil posted the biggest share, contributing about 287.9
million dollars or 70.3 percent to total first half export
earnings, followed by desiccated coconut and copra meal.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
