The former governor of the central province of Cebu earlier
also resigned as Executive Vice-president of the Lakas-NUCD to
ensure a "level playing field" among the party's presidential
aspirants.
</P>
<P>
Osmena, chairman of the presidential Committee on Flagship
Programs and Projects before submitting his letter of resignation,
was the brains behind the economic boom of Cebu.
