<HEADLINE> Forthcoming ECOWAS Summit to Boost Regional </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Heads of state and government of
the Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS) will begin
its 20th ordinary summit on August 28 in Abuja, capital of
Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
An official announcement said Wednesday the ECOWAS decision to
bring down the illegal government in Sierra Leone would be on the
summit agenda, and so would be the funding of the organization.
</P>
<P>
The two-day summit would review the schemes as well as work
out the modalities for its eventual take-off so as to further
promote security and economic integration in the sub-region, said
Ayo Ogunlade, Nigerian Minister of National Planning and Chairman
of the ECOWAS council of ministers.
</P>
<P>
According to Ogunlade, a series of meetings have already begun
ahead of the summit, including those of the administration and
finance commission, the economic and monetary affairs committee
and the ad-hoc committee of ECOWAS central bank governors.
</P>
<P>
They will be followed by a council of ministers meeting and
foreign ministers meeting.
</P>
<P>
The 16-member sub-regional organization, established in 1975,
is aimed at economic integration and a common market in the west
African sub-region.
</P>
<P>
The collective efforts in the past years have tightened
economic ties and promoted the movement of persons and goods
among member countries, although problems remain to be solved.
</P>
</TEXT>
