<HEADLINE> Colombia Downs Bolivia in World Cup Qualifyer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Colombia boosted its chances to
the 1998 World Cup in France after beating Bolivia 3-0 in a
qualifying match in Barranquilla of Colombia on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Anthony de Avila opened the scoring in the first minute with a
header. Carlos Valderrama and Faustino Asprilla rewrote the
scoring board in the 29th minute and 76th minute respectively.
</P>
<P>
Colombia now stands second to Argentina by one point behind in
South America region.
</P>
<P>
The top four teams from the region qualify for France. 
