<HEADLINE> Dole Seeks Bigger Share of China's Fruit Pie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- China has welcomed the Dole Food
Company of the US to put more into the country's agriculture with
foreign funds and technology.
</P>
<P>
Chinese State Councillor Chen Junsheng told Dole's chairman
David Murdock in a half-hour meeting in Beijing's Great Hall of
the People this afternoon, that China has great potential for
producing and marketing fruits.
</P>
<P>
Chen told Murdock, who is making his first visit to China, that
the fruit giant could invest in the horticultural industry in many
areas like fruit, flower, and vegetable growing, or in storage and
transport by providing much-needed funds and technology.
</P>
<P>
He praised the progress of a joint venture fruit project that
Dole has funded in Beihai in south China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region. and briefed him and his group on China's
agriculture production.
</P>
<P>
Murdock said that his company is willing to provide
state-of-the-art technology for Chinese fruit farmers to help them
produce more higher quality fruit and transport it to other parts
of the country. 
</P>
