<HEADLINE> Albania Urges Italy to Postpone Repatriating Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Albanian President Rexhep Mejdani
has appealed to the Italian government to put off its mass
repatriation of Albanian refugees.
</P>
<P>
The appeal came after an announcement by Italian Prime Minister
Romano Prodi two days earlier that Italy will repatriate all of
the 150,000 Albanian refugees by the end of this month.
</P>
<P>
In an open letter to the refugees released Wednesday, the
president hoped that the Italian government and parliament could
understand that any repatriation at this moment would cause
serious problems to the Albanian government.
</P>
<P>
"I hope the Italian government could find a more convenient
time and human way to repatriate those refugees," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian refugees had fled to avoid violence in the country
triggered by the failure of a fraudulent savings scheme earlier
this year. 
</P>
