<DOCNO> XIE19970821.0138 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB Helps Kyrgyz Create Rural Credit Unions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
today approved a 12.5 million U.S. dollar loan to the Kyrgyz
Republic to help it establish a rural credit union network.
</P>
<P>
The Rural Financial Institutions project, which represents a
move away from the traditional approach of providing rural credit
through financial institution, will help establish 280 credit
unions across the country's six regions.
</P>
<P>
The project, which is due for completion by September 2004, is
expected to cost a total of 22.1 million U.S. dollars, the ADB
said in a news release.
</P>
<P>
The ADB loan is interest-free, carries a service charge of 1
percent per annum and is repayable over 40 years, including a
10-year grace period, the bank said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
