<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Regional Life Insurance Meeting To be Held in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 21 (Xinhua) -- More than 8,000 life insurance
 practitioners from the Asia-Pacific region will share their
experience in insurance business at a four-day conference which is
 to open in Hong Kong tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
There will be about 70 keynote speeches, workshops and
exhibitions during the fourth Asia Pacific Life Insurance Congress
 (APLIC), the theme of which is "The New Horizon".
</P>
<P>
Some 50 renowned insurance professionals from around the world
will deliver speeches at the Congress to share their experience
and skills among the participants.
</P>
<P>
Tony Mak, chairman of the APLIC, told a news briefing here
today that Hong Kong being chosen as the host of Asia's largest
life insurance congress this year "signifies international
confidence in Hong Kong's insurance industry after the handover."
Preparations for the insurance gala started two years ago.
</P>
<P>
Life insurance industry has great potential in the Asia-Pacific
 market, he said. Only 40 to 50 percent of Hong Kong's whole
population are life insurance policy holders -- a ratio much lower
 than that of the developed market in the U.S. and Europe, and the
 current total premium income of life insurance account for a
small proportion of the GDP in the region.
</P>
<P>
With the aging of population, the protection of the elderly has
 become a worldwide concern. Mak said that when more and more
people become aware of the need for life insurance, the industry
will brace for promising prospects.
</P>
<P>
This year's Congress is hosted by the Life Underwriters
Association of Hong Kong, which has 22,000 registered insurance
practitioners.
</P>
<P>
Held every two years in different cities in the Asia-Pacific
Region, the APLIC held its first three congresses in Singapore,
Malaysia and Australia. The next APLIC will be held in the
Philippines.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
