<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Six Japanese Climbers Killed by Avalanche in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 21 (Xinhua) -- An heavy avalanche killed six
Japanese climbers and injured other five in their base camp in
northern Pakistan's Karakoram mountain range, tour officials said
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Three Pakistani guides also were injured when the avalanche
enveloped the 16-member expedition's base camp early on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The group, which had successfully scaled the 7,360-meter Mount
Skilbrum on Sunday, had been resting at the base camp at 5,300
meters. They had been scheduled to return to Islamabad later on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani military helicopters evacuated the surviving Japanese
and Pakistanis. All eight were injured, one critically, but were
in a stable condition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
