<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dengfeng Endeavors to Become Fine Tourist City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Tourists who visit China's
famous Shaolin Temple may be surprised to find that Dengfeng, in
Henan province, where it's located, is a clean and beautiful city.
</P>
<P>
This was not the case just a few years ago, when the city gave
people the impression of being dirty and dishevelled.
</P>
<P>
Dengfeng remained a poor mountain city until the Shaolin Temple
became known to the world in film made in the early 1980s.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of tourists visit the temple and the Shaolin style of
martial arts every year, bringing a tremendous amount of money to
the backward city, and at the same time raising new questions for
the local government about how to turn the city into a modern
tourist center that meets tourist needs.
</P>
<P>
The government has built new tourist attractions, but has
decided to beautify the city as well, and has already spent 200
million yuan (24 million US dollars) on 10 key clean-up, road
improvement, lighting, and pollution control projects.
</P>
<P>
So far, 19 major roads have been built, 850 roads asphalted,
more than 300 flower beds built along streets, over 40,000 trees
planted, and 150,000 sq.m. of lawn planted. And, two garden-parks
have been added.
</P>
<P>
In order to reduce pollution, the city has also built a sewage
treatment plant with a daily capacity of 5000 tons, and 10 garbage
disposal stations and a non-toxic garbage treatment plant.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the city has also opened six scenic areas and is
offering several tourist routes that feature martial arts,
religion, geology, archeology, astronomy, and mountain climbing.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
