<HEADLINE> Ukrainian PM Inaugurates Opening of Polyethylene Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 20 (Xinhua) -- While on a working tour around the
country, Ukrainian Prime Minister Valeriy Pustovoitenko today
inaugurated the opening ceremony of a Polyethylene Plant, the
National News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Polyethylene Plant, a joint venture with Germany's Linde, is
located in Kalush, one of Ukraine's major chemical centers in
Ivano-Frankovsk State in the western part of the country.
</P>
<P>
Stepan Chernyk, president of the plant's parent company Oriana
Concert, said that the plant can manufacture more than 40 kinds of
products of high, medium and low density on a single production
line.
</P>
<P>
He added the construction of the plant was prompted by the
growing demand in the domestic market, and the fact that Kalush is
Ukraine's major producer and exporter of ethylene, the basic raw
material for making polyethylene. 
</P>
