<DOCNO> XIE19970821.0163 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Manufacturing Sector Posts Poor Showing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' manufacturing
sector failed to sustain its recovery in June as its value and
volume indices both fell considerably compared with the year-ago
levels, the National Statistics Office said today.
</P>
<P>
On a year-on-year basis, the Value of Production Index (VPI) in
key manufacturing enterprises fell by 5.3 percent to 433.8 in June
while the Volume of Production Index (VoPI) in the sector dropped
by 5.1 percent to 147.2, according to figures released by the
office.
</P>
<P>
The statistics office conducts a survey of key enterprises in
manufacturing monthly in order to provide flash indicators on the
performance of the manufacturing sector.
</P>
<P>
The VoPI, derived from the VPI and producers' price index with
1992 as a base year, is a measure of manufacturing output adjusted
for inflation.
</P>
<P>
The manufacturing sector, which usually contributes more than
22 percent to the country's gross national product (GNP),
performed poorly during the first quarter. But it recovered
significantly in April with its volume index gained a 9.3-percent
growth.
</P>
<P>
On a month-on-month comparison, the VPI slightly increased by
0.6 percent compared with May while the VoPI rose 0.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
On a year-on-year basis, decreases in value of production were
observed in 10 out of 16 major sub-sectors, including petroleum
products, food manufacturing, textile and transport equipment.
</P>
<P>
Among the gainers were electrical machinery, non-metallic
mineral products and beverage.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, double-digit annual decreases in volume were
registered in seven sub-sectors, including petroleum refineries,
textile, wearing apparel and paper and paper products.
</P>
<P>
Among the volume decliners were electrical machinery,
non-metallic mineral products, beverage and food manufacturing.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970821.0164 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
