<HEADLINE> Italian Foilers Aim at Domination of Universiade Fencing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Foilers from world fencing
powerhouse Italy are aiming at the domination of fencing tournament of
the 19th World University Games which begins here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The tournament will begin with the men's individual foil. The
Italians field a strong team in the event, including 24-year-old
Gabriele Magni, substitute at the 1996 Atlanta Olympics and the
recently held world championships in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
The Italians will face the challenges from the strong opponents
from Russia, Hungary and Cuba. China, which also send their best
foilers to the Universiade, is also capable of making some upsets.
</P>
<P>
In the women's foil, defending champion and Olympic champion
Valentina Vezzali is the favorite.
</P>
<P>
But it will not be easy for Vezzali to win the title at Sicily
Universiade because of the quality of the participants. Among her
opponents are Olympic chamipion Laura Badea of Romania and foilers
from France and Hungary.
</P>
<P>
"It will be a difficult tournament to win," said the 27-year-old
Badea, "there are many strong opponents. Among them are the
Hungarians, the French and the Italians."
</P>
<P>
Badea finished a disappointing fifth at Fukuoka Universiade two
years ago. But two years later at Sicily, she is now one of the
best female foilers in the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
