<HEADLINE> Local Media Praise Chinese Football Team at Universiade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Local media praised
Chinese football team after they became the first team to advance
into the quarter-finals of the 19th World University Games.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday evening, the Chinese eleven beat Nigeria 2-1 for
their second straight victory in group D. They trounced Czech
Republic 4-0 in their first outing on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The two victories gave the Chinese team six points and ensured them
a place in the quarter-finals after the United States were forced to a
2-2 draw by Czech Republic in the other group D match on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The local media were surprised to see that it was the Chinese team
but not the Italian team to enter the quarter-finals first. But they
gave the right response immediately by praising the Chinese players as
"talented" and "promising".
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, the same one which took part in the World Youth
Championships in Malaysia in May, are not in their full strength as
four players have been called to the Chinese national team while three
more players didn't come to the Universiade due to injury. 
</P>
