<HEADLINE> Kenya to Host G-77 Trade Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The G-77 Chambers of Commerce
and Industry (CCI) of developing countries will begin a three-day
meeting here September 1 over the establishment of the first
G-77 bank in kenya and other issues.
</P>
<P>
The Kenya Commercial Bank now is putting final touches on the
feasibility study on the proposed G-77 Trade and Development Bank
and is expected to table the document at the meeting, the Kenya
Times newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
All 21 member states of the G-77 steering committee are
expected to send delegates to the three-day meeting, sponsored by
the Kenya National Chamber of Commerce and Industry.
</P>
<P>
Some 10 other participants are expected from the group's
headquarters in Karachi, Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The G-77 group, comprising 132 developing countries from Asia,
Africa, Latin America, and the Pacific and Carribean region, was
founded at the first U.N. Conference on Trade and Development
meeting in Geneva in 1964.
</P>
<P>
The group set up CCI in 1986 in a bid to mobilize the
participation of their private sector for economic development.
</P>
</TEXT>
