<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Starts Malaysia Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng
arrived here today for a four-day official visit to Malaysia, the
first leg of his two-nation Southeast Asian tour.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier came at the invitation of Malaysian Prime
Minister Mahathir Mohammed.
</P>
<P>
Li was greeted at the airport by Malaysian Foreign Minister
Abdullah Ahmad Badawi and Annuar Musa, chairman of the Malaysian
government receptionist committee and minister of rural
development.
</P>
<P>
In a written speech upon arrival, Li said China and Malaysia
are friendly neighbors and the two peoples enjoy profound
friendship.
</P>
<P>
He said that in recent years, thanks to joint efforts, the
bilateral relations between China and Malaysia have witnessed
rapid development, as evidenced by the frequent exchanges of
visits between the leaders of the two countries, satisfactory
results of cooperation in the economic and trade, cultural and
educational fields and a further strengthened traditional
friendship between the two peoples, said the Chinese premier.
</P>
<P>
"My current visit to Malaysia will be one of friendship and
cooperation. I am looking forward to an in-depth exchange of views
with Prime Minister Mahathir and other Malaysian leaders on
bilateral relations and issues of mutual interest," Li said.
</P>
<P>
"I would also like to take this opportunity to see for myself
new achievements Malaysia has registered in recent years in its
economic and social development," he said.
</P>
<P>
Li last visited Malaysia in December 1990. "I hope my current
visit will further enhance the mutual understanding and friendship
between our two countries and push the bilateral friendly
cooperation to a new high," he said.
</P>
<P>
Li's entourage includes his wife Zhu Lin, Deputy
Secretary-General of the State Council He Chunlin, Minister of
Machine-Building Industry Bao Xuding, Director of the Foreign
Affairs Office of the State Council Liu Huaqiu, Director of the
Research Office of the State Council Wang Mengkui, Vice-Foreign
Minister Tang Jiaxuan.
</P>
<P>
Shortly after his arrival, Li was accorded a grand welcome
ceremony at the Parliament Square in downtown Kuala Lumpur.
Accompanied by Mahathir, Li reviewed the guard of honor of the
Malaysian army.
</P>
<P>
During his visit here, Li will meet Malaysian Supreme Head of
State Tuanku Ja'afar, and confer with Mahathir on promoting the
bilateral relations between China and Malaysia and on other issues
of mutual interest.
</P>
<P>
After his visit to Malaysia, Li will travel to neighboring
Singapore for a three-day official visit at the invitation of his
Singaporean counterpart Goh Chok Tong.  
</P>
</TEXT>
