<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fourth World Youth Fin-Swimming Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Russian fin-swimmers wrapped up
four gold medals and Chinese chalked up the rest two on the first
day of the fourth World Youth Fin-Swimming Championship at
Balaton, Hungary on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Russians collected the titles through Oksana Koroleva in the
women's 400 meters bated breath diving at three minutes 37.42
seconds, Ilja Uljanov in the men's 200m fin-swimming at 1:29.93,
Pavel Ivanov in the men's 800m fin-swimming at 6:50.86 and the
women quartet in the 4x100m fin-swimming relay at 6:55.20.
</P>
<P>
Li Jin won the men's 100 meter apparatus for China with a
clocking of 38.38 seconds and his teammate Yin Jun added the
second one in the women's 50m bated breath diving at 18.22.
</P>
<P>
The four-day championship, which attracted more than 200
fin-swimmers from 23 countries and regions, will end on Saturday.
</P>
</TEXT>
