<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand share market
rose again today after another solid close on Wall Street
overnight.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 14 points higher at 2,517 with a
turnover of 64 million New Zealand dollars (41 million U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Telecom shares led the rises, up 7 cents to 756 cents. Also
higher were Fletcher Paper, edging up 2 cents to 344 cents;
Fletcher Energy, jumping 22 cents to 582 cents; and Lion Nathan,
climbing 7 cents to 407 cents.
</P>
<P>
Brierley Investment remained steady at 139 cents.
</P>
<P>
Carter Holt Harvey fell 4 cents to 346 cents and Air New
Zealand dipped 2 cents to 296 cents.  
</P>
</TEXT>
