<HEADLINE> Cambodian Co-Ministers of Defense Leave for Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Co-Ministers of
Defense, Tea Banh and Tea Chanrath left here today for the Thai
capital Bangkok on a mission centering on the repatriation of
thousands of Cambodian refugees recently fleeing the country.
</P>
<P>
Speaking before their departure, Tea Banh said they will hold
talks with their Thai counterpart and Prime Minister Chavalit
Yongchaiyudh to arrange the details of the repatriation.
</P>
<P>
He also reiterated the government's pledge of ensuring the safe
return of Cambodian politicians currently on exile in Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Fightings broke out a few days ago as Cambodian government
forces fought to seize the last stronghold held by loyalists of
the ousted First Prime Minister Prince Nordodom Ranariddh.
</P>
<P>
The fighting caused an exodus of about 300,000 Cambodian
refugees, mostly women and children, to the neighboring Thailand.
</P>
</TEXT>
