<HEADLINE> Krishan Kant Sworn in as Indian Vice President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 21 (Xinhua)-- Former governor of Andhra
Pradesh Krishan Kant was sworn in today as the 10th vice president
of India, the Press Trust of India reported.
</P>
<P>
Kant, a joint candidate of the ruling United Front and the
Congress party, was elected vice president in a poll on August 16
after defeating his sole rival, Surjeet Singh Barnala, who was
backed by the opposition Bharatiya Janata Party and its allies.
</P>
<P>
Kant is a veteran freedom fighter and a school-and-college
friend of Prime Minister Inder Kumar Gujral. 
</P>
</TEXT>
