<HEADLINE> Uganda to Help Immunize Congolese Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Health officials from Uganda
will go to the Democratic Republic of Congo to immunize
children there against polio, reported the local daily "The New
Vision" today.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the need to help Congo immunize childern, Ugandan
Minister of Health Crispus Kiyonga said that it is useless for
Ugandans to immunize all the children against polio while
neighbors are bringing back the virus.
</P>
<P>
"We shall also do it for our neighbors," he added.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, several non-governmental
organisations in Uganda will provide assistance to enable trained
Ugandans go to Kinshasa, capital of the Democratic Congo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
