<HEADLINE> Urgent: Chinese Premier Arrives in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng
arrived here this afternoon on a four-day official visit to
Malaysia, the first leg of his two-nation Southeast Asian tour.
</P>
<P>
This is Li Peng's second trip to Malaysia as guest of Prime
Minister Mahathir Mohammed, the last one in December 1990.
</P>
<P>
Li was greeted at the airport by Malaysian Foreign Minister
Abdullah Ahmad Badawi and Annuar Musa, chairman of the Malaysian
government reception committee and minister of rural development.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, Li is scheduled to confer with Mahathir
on promoting the Sino-Malaysian relations and on other issues of
common concern.
</P>
<P>
After Malaysia, Li will proceed to neighboring Singapore on
August 24 on a three-day official visit at the invitation of his
Singaporean counterpart Goh Chok Tong.  
</P>
