<DOCNO> XIE19970821.0195 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colombia Virtually Qualify for World Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Colombia virtually assured
themselves of a place in the World Cup finals in France with a 3-0
victory over Bolivia on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
After the day's qualifiers, Peru, Uruguay and Ecuador revived
their chances of entering the finasl with previous wins.
</P>
<P>
Argentina and Paraguay look set to join Colombia, but the race
for the last of South America's qualifying places in next year's
World Cup was thrown wide open by Uruguay's 1-0 win over Chile.
</P>
<P>
The gap between fourth-placed Chile and eighth-placed Uruguay
was reduced to two points as three teams in the lower half of the
table scored important wins.
</P>
<P>
In addition to Uruguay, Peru cruised to a 3-0 win away to
minnows Venezuela while Ecuador came from behind for a 2-1 win
over Paraguay, who could have gone top of the single South
American group if they had won in Quito.
</P>
<P>
Argentina, who had the night off, still top the table with 25
points, followed by Colombia with 24 and Paraguay with 23. Chile
and Peru have 19, Ecuador 18, Bolivia and Uruguay 17 and hapless
Venezuela just three.
</P>
<P>
Each team has three games left, apart from Colombia, Ecuador
and Venezuela, who have only two.
</P>
<P>
Argentina and Colombia are both one victory away from France
and as Colombia's next game is at home to Venezuela, they look set
to clinch their place in September.
</P>
<P>
Paraguay still have home games against Bolivia, who have only
taken one away point, and Venezuela and so should also secure the
four points they need fairly comfortably.
</P>
<P>
Chile play their last three matches at home, where they have a
100 percent record, but their next fixture is against Argentina, a
team against whom they tend to suffer from an inferiority complex.
</P>
<P>
The Peruvians have two home games left but their match in Chile
in October is likely to prove crucial. Uruguay's next game is
away to Peru, before they travel to Buenos Aires to face
arch-rivals Argentina in October. Bolivia's remaining fixtures
are all tough away games and their chances look minimal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
