<HEADLINE> Sydney Plans to Tour Olympic Torch in Islands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Sydney 2000 Olympic Organisers
is planning to take the Olympic flame on an island hopping tour of
the South Pacific.
</P>
<P>
Australia's International Olympic Committee member Phil Coles
said he wants to spread the Olympic message throughout the region
by including small island nations in the torch relay.
</P>
<P>
"We are currently trying to work our way through a plan to take
the torch to each of the Oceania countries that have an Olympic
committee," Coles said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Coles added there were about 10 South Pacific island nations
with Olympic committees, such as the Solomon Islands, Nauru, Papua
New Guinea, Fiji, the Cook Islands, Tonga and New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
He said the proposal would be put to the heads of state at next
month's South Pacific Forum in the Cook Islands.
</P>
<P>
The Olympic flame will be ignited from the sun ray's at Olympia
in Greece about five month's before the September 16 opening
ceremony of the Sydney Olympics. 
