<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chittagong Port Users Out Against Surcharge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The users of Chittagong port are
contemplating legal action against the Chittagong Feeder Trade
Committee (CFTC) for imposing an "illegal" congestion surcharge at
Bangladesh's premier sea port, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
"If possible, we'll go for legal action," said Ahmed Chowdhury,
leader of the Bangladeshi delegation which negotiated with the
CFTC in Singapore early this month.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore-based CFTC imposed congestion surcharge for a
month from August 16 following its unsuccessful talks with the
port users. The surcharge was fixed at the rate of 150 U.S.
dollars for a 20-foot container and 300 dollars for a 40-foot
container per day.
</P>
<P>
Chowdhury said as per the code of conduct of the UN convention
on shipping, the CFTC could not explain valid reasons or account
for the surcharge before the users.
</P>
<P>
"It is contrary to the international shipping convention.
Therefore, imposition of any such surcharge by the CFTC is totally
illogical and illegal," he said.
</P>
<P>
Chittagong port officials admitted that there was congestion at
the port in early July following heavy rains and a five-day
partial work stoppage by the workers but the situation has become
almost normal for regular handling of cargo vessels.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Chowdhury appealed to all to keep the Chittagong
port out of the purview of all kinds of political or other
programs for the sake of the country's economy. He also asked the
government to improve the port facilities and curb labor unrest.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore-based feeder operators had imposed congestion
surcharge off and on from 1992 as a result of shortage of
container handling equipment and space in container yards and
unusual strikes.
</P>
<P>
The CFTC's latest congestion surcharge was imposed in September
1995 and was lifted on July 1, 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970821.0208 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
