<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Finnish, Chinese Military Leaders Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Finland's Commander-in-Chief of
Defense Forces Gustav Hagglund today met with Fu Quanyou, chief of
the General Staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA),
and both sides agreed to strengthen exchanges and cooperation
between the two armies.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Fu, who is also member of the Chinese
Central Military Commission, briefed Finnish officials and
officers on China's foreign policy, domestic situation, national
defense policy and the PLA.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese people love and cherish peace, and China
will unswervingly stick to an independent peace-oriented foreign
policy, and will be committed to safeguarding world peace and
promoting common development.
</P>
<P>
On China's national defense policy, Fu pointed out that China
pursues a military strategic policy of active self-defense, and
opposes hegemonism.
</P>
<P>
At a banquet in honor of the Chinese general, Hagglund said
that Finland is willing to establish and maintain a long-term
friendly and cooperative relationship with China.
</P>
<P>
Fu said that China and Finland have no conflict of interests,
and developing and consolidating the stable, long-term friendly
cooperative relations between the two countries and the two armies
conform with the two people's interests and are beneficial to
world peace, stability and development.
</P>
<P>
Fu arrived here earlier today for a five-day official visit,
after visiting the United States where he met with U.S. government
and military leaders.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Fu is expected to hold talks with President
Martti Ahtisaari, Defense Minister Anneli Taina and Hagglund. He
will also visit the three services of the Finnish army. 
</P>
