<HEADLINE> Hungarian Opposition Opposes Government Joining NATO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Hungarian Workers' Party
Chairman Thurmer Gyula said here today that his party strongly
opposed the Hungarian government joining the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO).
</P>
<P>
Thurmer made the remarks at a mass rally to mark the country's
Constitution Day.
</P>
<P>
Faced with a historic choice, he said, Hungary would lose her
independence won not long before if she joins the NATO.
</P>
