agreed to provide a short-term bridging facility to the Bank of
Thailand in support of the country's "economic adjustments"
pending the drawdown of part of the International Monetary Fund
facility now being arranged.
</P>
<P>
"As a member of the BIS, the HKMA has agreed to join the
central banks or monetary authorities of the G-10 countries and
other Asian and European economies in guaranteeing the bridging
facility by the BIS," the release said.
</P>
<P>
It stressed that the participation of Hong Kong, which is a
leading financial center in Asia and full member of the BIS, is a
reflection of Hong Kong's commitment to financial stability in the
region.  
