<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liaoning Wins Chinese Women's Basketball League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The Liaoning Club shocked the
August First 72-61 in the second game of the final to win the 97'
Chinese Women's Basketball League in Shenyang on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Liaoning, runner-up in the last season, beat the August
First 80-69 in the first game of the final last week.
</P>
<P>
The August First, which dominated the women's sport in China in
the past decade, displayed an unstable performance Wednesday night
with the absence of 2.05-center Zheng Haixia, who now plays in the
Los Angeles Sparks of WNBA.
</P>
<P>
Less than 10 minutes into the game, the host team jumped to
lead by 12 points, but it did not keep its pace in the rest of the
first half.
</P>
<P>
The August First, which intensified the interior defends,
narrowed the margin to two points at halftime.
</P>
<P>
After the interval, the Army team once led the score at 40-39.
However, the host team, with successive three-pointers, took the
lead again and widened the margin by 15 points before taking the
crown.
</P>
<P>
In the play-off for third place, the Harbin defeated the
Sichuan 87-67 in Harbin, capital of Heilongjiang Province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
