<DOCNO> XIE19970821.0230 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia, Malaysia to Build World's Longest Bridge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government has
agreed the plan to build with Malaysia a 95-kilometer-long bridge
connecting the Malaysian Peninsula and the Sumatra island,
official sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
President Soeharto gave his blessing Wednesday for the project,
which will be carried out by a private consortium of Indonesian
and Malaysian companies, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
The 36-meter-wide bridge will be built in five years. 42
kilometers of the bridge will span the Malacca Strait, another 47
kilometers will be above an island and another 6 kilometers will
be on the shores of Riau province, Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
The sources did not disclose the estimated cost of the bridge,
which they said would be the longest in the world. As many as
5,000 vehicles are expected to use the bridge daily, they added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
