<HEADLINE> Seles Advances at Hardcourt Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Second seed Monica Seles
cruised to a comfortable 6-4, 6-3 victory over Japan's Naoko
Sawamatsu in a second round match at the 450,000-dollar
U.S. Women's Hardcourt Championships held at Atlanta on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Seles recovered from 3-1 down in the first set to lash out 10
aces en route to the final victory.
</P>
<P>
Top seed Jana Novotna of the Czech Republic, out of competition
since July 13 through injury, needed three sets to beat Yayuk
Basuki of Indonesia 4-6, 6-2, 6-2 in a rain-delayed second-round
match.
</P>
<P>
Seventh seed Ruxandra Dragomir of Romania was the only upset
victim, beaten by Australian Open quarter-finalist Dominique van
Roost of Belgium 6-0, 6-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
