<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rio Group Summit to Discuss Regional Integration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Heads of state from the
Rio Group will hold a summit in Paraguay to discuss regional
integration, Brazilian Foreign Ministry spokesman said here today.
</P>
<P>
At the summit scheduled for Saturday and Sunday in Asuncion,
participants will mediate the row between Argentina and Brazil
over Brazil's bid for a permanent seat on the U.N. Security
Council, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
Argentine President Carlos Menem told a Brazilian newspaper
earlier that his administration opposed Brazil's bid for the seat
because that would destroy "regional balance."
</P>
<P>
Brazilian government refuted Menem's statement, saying it
violated the Rio Group rules.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman announced that Brazilian President Fernando
Cardoso will discuss the issue with Menem during the summit.
</P>
<P>
The Rio Group, founded in 1986, aims to promote the region's
economic integration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
