<HEADLINE> China's Industrial Output Value Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The latest statistics from State
Statistics Bureau show that China generated an industrial output
value of 649.3 billion yuan last June, up 14.3 percent over
the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The light industry turned out 288.2 billion yuan worth-of goods
last June, up 15.7 percent, while the output of the heavy industry
was worth 361.1 billion yuan, up 13.2 percent.  
</P>
