<HEADLINE> Myanmar, Thailand to Survey Boundary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar and Thailand have agreed
to conduct a survey of their common boundary which stretches over
2,000 kilometers, The New Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached at the Third Meeting of Myanmar-Thai
Joint Border Committee held in Bangkok Tuesday following
discussions between Myanmar Deputy Foreign Minister U Nyunt Swe
and his Thai counterpart Pitak Intrawrtnayunt.
</P>
<P>
In May, prime ministers of Myanmar and Thailand met in the
Myanmar capital of Yangon and agreed to expedite the demarcation
of their boundary.
</P>
<P>
Both sides expressed the desire to turn their common border
between the two nations into a border of friendship, harmony and
prosperity.  
</P>
</TEXT>
