<HEADLINE> Ukraine, U.S. Discuss Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian Prime Minister Valeriy
Pustovoitenko met United States Ambassador to the United Nations
Bill Richardson here today to discuss political and economic
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Richardson said after the meeting that both sides exchanged
views on how to strengthen the functioning of the Kuchma-Gore
committee to step up the economic reforms in Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
Pustovoitenko said the new Ukrainian government under his
leadership will not deviate from economic reforms. Ukraine needs
financial support and assistance from the United States and
international financial organizations more earnestly than ever
before, he added.
</P>
<P>
Richardson said that relations between the United States and
Ukraine have seen great improvements since 1991 and have reached
the level of a strategic partnership.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed United Nations reforms.
</P>
<P>
Richardson said he would keep in close contact with Ukrainian
Foreign Minister Gennady Udovenko, who holds the current
presidency of the UN General Assembly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
