<HEADLINE> Portugal Seals Comfortable 3-1 Win over Armenia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Portugal kept alive their hopes
of reaching next year's World Cup finals with a comfortable 3-1
win over Armenia in a European group nine qualifier on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Portugal are still third-placed in the group, level on points
with second-placed Germany but having played one more games. The
group leader is Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Pedro Barbosa opened the account for Portugal at the
22nd minutes and Barcelona's Luis Figo scored a second eight
minutes later before Eric Assadourian pulled one back for Armenia
in the first minute of the second half.
</P>
<P>
Portugese victory went beyond doubt in the 53rd minute when
Pedro Barbosa fired home from close range a poor back pass.
</P>
