<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania Qualify for World Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Romania became the first European
team to qualify for the World Cup finals when they beat Macedonia
4-2 in Bucharest on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ireland's 0-0 home draw with Lithuania meant that the
Romanians, quarter-finalists in 1994, cannot be caught in group
eight after winning all seven qualifiers to date.
</P>
<P>
Two goals by Viorel Moldovan and one each for Constatin Galca
and Ilie Dumitrescu rewarded Romania the honor as the first
European qualifier.
</P>
<P>
Three times winners Germany looked on course for an
embarrassment against Northern Ireland in Belfast when Michael
Hughes scored in the 59th minute for the home team. Substitute
Oliver Bierhoff played the Savior by scoring a hat-trick in six
minutes to earn a 3-1 victory.
</P>
<P>
Germany stay second, two points behind Ukraine in group nine
with two games in hand. Ukraine needed a goal three minutes from
time by Serhiy Rebrov to beat Albania while third placed Portugal
play Armenia later on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Group one provided the night's surprise when Bosnia beat
Denmark 3-0 to blow the group wide open.
</P>
<P>
The Danes still head the standings by three points but still
have to play their main challengers Greece and Croatia.
</P>
<P>
A second half hat-trick from veteran striker Anton Polster gave
Austria a 3-0 win against Estonia in group four and Sweden kept
close by caming from behind to win 2-1 in Belarus.
</P>
<P>
Scotland still lead the group with 17 points with Austria
second on 16 and Sweden third on 15.
</P>
<P>
Turkey kept alive their slim chances in group seven by beating
Wales 6-4 in a remarkable game in Istanbul where striker Hakan
Sukur scored four goals.
</P>
<P>
Despite the victory Turkey are still unlikely to qualify as the
Netherlands and Belgium are five points clear with the top three
each having two games left.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria's Lyuboslav Penev hit the only goal of the game after
69 minutes in Sofia to take his country to the top of group five.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria now have 15 points, one ahead of Russia. They have
been guaranteed the top two places in the group, with top spot yet
to be contested.
</P>
<P>
Iceland collected their first win of the campaign with a 4-0
victory over point-less Liechtenstein in group eight. 
</P>
</TEXT>
