<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Ireland's triple Olympic champion
Michelle de Bruin picked up her second gold in the women's 200
meters freestyle at the European Swimming Championships in
Seville, Spain on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
De Bruin, who used her maiden name of Smith at Atlanta,
continued her winning streak after Tuesday's 400 meters individual
medley with a career best in the 200m freestyle final.
</P>
<P>
