strong final strokes while breaking the two minutes barrier for
the first time as her personal best, and edged the second
Chemezova by just 0.04 seconds,
</P>
<P>
The 16-year-old Hungarian Agnes Kovacs, Olympic bronze
medalist, bettered her own European record of 2:25.31 to win the
women's 200 meters breaststroke in 2:24.90 which was just 0.26
seconds slower than the world record set by Australia's Rebecca
Brown.
</P>
