<HEADLINE> Unique Mobility Eyes U.S. Bike Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. company Unique
Mobility Inc. has set a target of seizing 10 percent of the
U.S. bicycle market by introducing an electric-powered model.
</P>
<P>
The new model, due to be on market next June, would make up a
tenth of the current yearly sales of 10 million bikes in the
United States, or one million bikes, Lee Iacocca, the company's
biggest shareholder, told the company's annual shareholders'
meeting in Golden, Colorado, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Iacocca, former chairman of the automobile giant Chrysler, said
an "electric revolution" is starting with bicycles and would
spread to the car industry, according to his 50-year experience in
the auto industry.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that about one million Americans have bicycles
and a growing number of people bike to work. 
</P>
