<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nuclear Plant Computer System Sold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- China has developed a new
nuclear power plant computer system, which will be exported to
Pakistan, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
The Distributed Control System, manufactured by the Beijing
Holysys Automation Co. Ltd., which is under the Sixth Research
Institute of the Ministry of the Electronics Industry, will serve
Chashma's 300 megawatt (MW) nuclear power plant.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a news conference yesterday, Wang Changli, general
manager of the company, said the computer system has been checked
and accepted by the departments concerned.
</P>
<P>
"This is the first time that we can export such a large-scale
hi-tech product to other countries," Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Wang said that after three years' effort, the computer system
has been brought up to advanced international standards in its
performance, function and reliability, based on co-operation
between the company and the Shanghai Nuclear Engineering Research
and Design Academy.
</P>
<P>
The company has also signed a contract with the Qinshan Nuclear
Power Plant to provide a computer control system for the plant's
second-phase project, which includes the installation of two 600
MW nuclear generators.
</P>
<P>
"The second-phase project needs high-quality and advanced
products and we believe our people currently have the ability to
produce advanced computer systems," said Zhang Huazhu, deputy
manager of the China Nuclear Industry Corp.
</P>
<P>
In other words, China can provide its own control system for
some State-level key projects instead of relying on products from
other countries, Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, China used a French computer control system in
its Daya Bay Nuclear Power Station and the first-phase project of
the Qinshan Nuclear Power Plant.
</P>
<P>
Since 1994, the Sixth Research Institute has developed two
kinds of distributed control system, which have become competitive
in the Chinese market against other world-renowned systems.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970821.0259 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
