<HEADLINE> Dockers on Strike in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTA FE DE BOGOTA, August 20 (Xinhua) -- More than 2,000
Colombian dock workers have begun a four-day strike in the
Buenaventura seaport, demanding freight and fuel price cuts, the
strike organizers said today.
</P>
<P>
The strike, called by the Colombian Association of Teamsters
(ACC), is in protest against middlemen's high freight charges and
the 8 percent rise on fuel prices decreed last week by the Mines
Ministry.
</P>
<P>
More than 800 trucks loaded with import and export goods
blocked the city, 300 kilometers southwest of the capital,
freezing cargo flow at the Pacific port and causing about one
million U.S. dollars loss, according to reports.
</P>
<P>
But ACC President Javier Suarez said the strike has not
affected ship-loading and about 1,000 trucks carry an average of
30,000 tons of goods to and from the port every day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
