the east sector of Lebanon's eastern Bekka Valley at 10:30 am
(7:30 GMT), injuring two children. (Lebanon-Israel-Raid)
</P>
<P>
LAGOS -- The military Junta in Sierra Leone has ordered a
curfew from 10:00 P.M. till 6:00 A.M. in an attempt to improve the
security situation in the capital Freetown.
</P>
<P>
The state radio, which announced the curfew Tuesday night, also
said the military government would take a number of touch measures
to crack down on possible trouble makers, with the possibility of
offenders to be shot on site. (SLeone-Curfew)
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iranian Parliament dominated by the conservatives
Wednesday approved all of the 22-ministers proposed by liberal
President Mohammad Khatami.
</P>
<P>
The vote in favor of Khatami's cabinet showed the power and
influence that the 54-year-old president has gained from the 62
million populated nation since his inauguration on August 4.
</P>
<P>
Kamal Kharrazi became the foreign minister, Ali Shamkhani the
defense minister, and Hossein Namazi the economic minister.
(Iran-Cabinet-Khatami) 
