Manila Bulletin
</P>
<P>
-- Senator Vicente Sotto, in an emotion-filled privilege speech
after weeks of being "pilloried" as a drug lord protector,
formally resigned Wednesday as chairman of the Senate Committee on
Illegal Drugs.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Journal
</P>
<P>
-- With the peso tumbling below the 30 pesos to one dollar
level at the Philippine Dealing System, the Central Bank Wednesday
indefinitely suspended its overnight lending facility as part of
its support to the local currency by siphoning off excess peso
liquidity.
</P>
<P>
Business World
</P>
<P>
-- Agila II, the first Filipino-owned and -managed
international telecommunications and broadcast satellite, was
finally launched into space early Wednesday morning from the
Xichang Satellite Launch Center in southwestern China.
</P>
<P>
Manila Standard
</P>
<P>
-- Four days of rain spawned by tropical storm have snuffed the
lives of 12 people and drove more than 265,000 from their homes,
officials of the National Disaster Coordinating Council said
Wednesday. 
