<DOCNO> XIE19970821.0269 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Earthquake Rocks Medan, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake registering 5.8 on
the Richter Scale Wednesday rumbled Medan, the capital of
Indonesia's north Sumatra province, causing panic among residents.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which hit the area at 2:15 p.m. local time, did not
claim lives or cause any significant damage of property, Antara
news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
An official of the Meteorological and Geophysical Office in
Medan said the three-to-five-second quake was also felt by people
in Banda Aceh, the capital of Aceh province.
</P>
<P>
The center of the quake was located at 3.8 degrees north
latitude and 96.05 degrees east longitude.
</P>
<P>
Many of the some 2 million residents of Medan panicked and ran
out of houses, offices and hotels, said the report.
</P>
<P>
An earthquake measuring 6 on the Richter Scale can cause severe
damage.  
</P>
</TEXT>
