<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Petrochemical Merger Approved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The State Council, China's
highest administrative body, has approved a proposed merger
between the Yihua Group Corp., Yangzi Petrochemical Corp., Jinling
Petrochemical Corp. and Nanjing Chemical Industrial Group.
</P>
<P>
According to today's"China Daily, a senior official with the
China National Textile Council said that the merger will help
stabilize the domestic chemical fiber market and help Yizheng, a
major chemical fiber producer in China, obtain a stable supply of
raw materials.
</P>
<P>
After merging, the group will become a conglomerate with total
assets reaching 50 billion yuan (about six billion US
dollars). Yizheng is one of the world's biggest polyester
manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
The official said that China's chemical fiber industry will
construct 20 large production bases of chemical fibers and raw
materials in the coming years and Yizheng is one of them.
</P>
<P>
Sources said the redundant construction of the four companies,
which are all located within 30 kilometers from Nanjing, capital
of Jiangsu Province, affected the utilization of resources and
weakened their own competitiveness. Experts said the four
companies should be suppliers of raw materials for each other.
</P>
<P>
Sources said a special company under the State Economic and
Trade Commission is expected to be established later this year to
become the holding company of the merged companies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
