<HEADLINE> Sweden Beat Belarus with Late Winner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Sweden scored twice in the last
15 minutes to beat Belarus 2-1 in Minsk in a World Cup European
group four qualifier on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Anderlecht striker Per Zetterberg found the winner five minutes
from time to send the Swedish side closer to group leaders
Scotland.
</P>
<P>
The home team took the lead in the 38th minute before Sweden's
second-half substitute Kennet Andersson equalised with 14 minutes
remaining.
</P>
<P>
Sweden are third in the group, two points behind Scotland with
a game in hand. Austria, who beat Estonia 3-0, are second, a
point ahead of the Swedes after the same number of games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
