<HEADLINE> Bierhoff Scores Hat-trick for Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Germany's substitude striker
Oliver Bierhoff scored a second half hat-trick within six minutes
to steer his country to a 3-1 victory over Northern Ireland in a
World Cup qualifier held at Belfast on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The home team led the score in the 59th minute through Michael
Hughes before Bierhoff, hero of Germany's Euro 96 triumph, struck
in the 72nd, 77th and 78th minutes.
</P>
<P>
Despite the win, the Germans stayed second in European group
nine, three points behind Ukraine but having two games in
hand. 
</P>
