<HEADLINE> Norway Sink Finns with Four Goals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Norway stormed to a 4-0 away
win over Finland on Wednesday to tighten their grip on World Cup
qualifying group three.
</P>
<P>
Now Norway head the group on 14 points and are almost certain
to make it to France with Hungary second on eight. Switzerland
are third on seven, ahead of Finland on goal difference.
</P>
<P>
The group leaders went ahead after eight minutes when Stale
Solbakken fired a shot past rookie goalkeeper Teuvo Moilanen.
</P>
<P>
It was 2-0 four minutes later when Petter Rudi scored with a
spectacular long shot.
</P>
<P>
Three minutes into the second half Jostein Flo hit the third
and Tore Andre Flo completed the victory six minutes from time.
</P>
