<HEADLINE> Missing U.S. Airman Found in Pelonnese Peninsula, Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Nine days after his
disappearance, Larry Gonzales, a U.S. airman stationed at the
Souda base on the Greek island of Crete, was found today by police
in Gytheio, a seaside town in Greece's Pelonnese peninsula, local
police announced today.
</P>
<P>
Police said in a press statement that 30-year-old Gonzales was
found today in a rented room in Gytheio, holidaying with a British
woman friend.
</P>
<P>
He was taken to a local police station from where he would be
turned over to officers of his unit.
</P>
<P>
Gonzales, who are reportedly responsible for analyzing
satellite messages, mysteriously disappeared on August 12 after
returning from work at the U.S. airbase to his hotel in Akrotiri.
</P>
<P>
Greek police and U.S. secret services had launched a search for
Gonzales since then. 
</P>
</TEXT>
