<HEADLINE> US Dollar Hits 10-Month Low Against Peso </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. dollar dropped to a
10-month low against the peso today on signs of an economic
rebound in Mexico, and also fell against the yen amid fears of
escalating trade friction between the United States and Japan.
</P>
<P>
In late New York trading, the dollar settled at 7.7450 pesos,
down from 7.750 Tuesday and its lowest level since 7.7410 on
October 21, 1996.
</P>
<P>
Also in New York, the dollar was quoted at 117.75 yen, down
from 118.21 late Tuesday. It rose to 1.8567 marks from 1.8388
Tuesday on the stability of German interest rates.
</P>
<P>
Other late dollar rates in New York, compared with late
Tuesday: 1.5242 Swiss francs, up from 1.5146; 6.2470 French
francs, up from 6.2022; 1,807.50 Italian lire, up from 1,793.80;
and 1.3927 Canadian dollars, down from 1.3943. The British pound
was quoted at 1.5940 U.S. dollars, down from 1.6054. 
</P>
</TEXT>
