<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Rebounds Further </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial
average rolled to its third consecutive 100-point gain today,
pushing back above 8,000 mark.
</P>
<P>
The Dow, which rose 108 points Monday and nearly 115 Tuesday,
jumped another 103.13 at 8,021.23. The blue-chip average is now up
more than 24 percent on the year, but still stays about 238 points
below its record close at 8,259.31 set on August 6.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 27.96 to 1,628.67, less than two
points shy of its record close of 1,630.44, also set August 6.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by more than a 2-to-1
margin on the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,954 up, 901 down and
546 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume totaled 518.14 million shares as of 4 p.m., vs.
545.58 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 13.34 to 939.35, the
NYSE composite index rose 4.29 to 483.83, and the American Stock
Exchange composite index rose 5.54 to 646.76.
</P>
<P>
The Commerce Department reported this morning that the U.S.
trade deficit narrowed sharply to 8.2 billion U.S. dollars in June
as American exports climbed to an all-time high and imports shrank
for the first time in eight months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
