<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy Score First Victory in Universiade Football </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Hosts Italy scored their
first goal and their first victory at the football tournament of the
19th World University Games at Palermo on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Italian team, who were forced to a goalless draw by their
Brazilian counterparts on Monday, played a nervous game in the first
half against Iran.
</P>
<P>
They could not find the way of breaking the tight defence of
their Iranian opponents while their goal-keeper was also seldom
tested in the first half.
</P>
<P>
After the tedious first half, the Italian team quickened their pace
and launched more counter-attacks against the Iranian team. But their
team work were not good enough to have the attacks well organized.
</P>
<P>
The angry Italian coach Ahmad Khodadkashi was very much
disappointed when the he saw the score was still deadlocked at 0-0 at
the 65th minute. "We are playing against a strong team and I think
the match will probably end at 0-0." Khodadhashi said when he was
interviewed by local TV station.
</P>
<P>
But only seven minutes later, the Italian team launched a quick
counter-attack. With only two crosses, Luca Ulivi completed the
mission as he beat the desperate Iranian goalie Sasan Naimyzaghiani.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian team then went all out to offence and forced the
Italian team back to defence. But the Italian goalie made some
brave saves to keep the 1-0 lead to the final whistle.
</P>
<P>
In the other group A match, Brazil beat Britain 3-2 to top the
group with more goals scored.
</P>
<P>
It was the British team which scored first. But the Brazilian
team soon levelled the score at 1-1 and surged ahead to take the
lead 2-1.
</P>
<P>
Though Britain levelled the score again in the second half, the
Brazilian refused to give up and finally got the winner.
</P>
<P>
Group B also had two matches on Wednesday with Morocco beat
Japan 1-0 and Ireland drew with Ukraine 0-0.
</P>
<P>
South Korea beat South Africa 1-0 while the other match of group C
between the Netherlands and Uruguay ended at 4-0 with the Dutch
turned to be the winners.
</P>
<P>
In group D, China scored their second consecutive victory by
beating Nigeria 2-1. The victory put China atop the group with six
points and ensured their qualification to the second round.
</P>
<P>
The United States were forced to a 2-2 draw by Czech Republic
and placed second with four points. On Monday, the American beat
Nigeria 4-0 in their first group match.
</P>
<P>
China will take on the United States while Nigeria will play
Czech Republic on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970821.0292 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-21 </DATE_TIME>
